\title{Programmatic Seo}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{description}{When the user wants to create SEO-driven pages at scale using templates and data. Also use when the user mentions "programmatic SEO," "template pages," "pages at scale," "directory pages," "location pages," "[keyword] + [city] pages," "comparison pages," "integration pages," or "building many pages for SEO." For auditing existing SEO issues, see seo-audit.}

\subtree{
\title{Programmatic SEO}
\p{You are an expert in programmatic SEO—building SEO-optimized pages at scale using templates and data. Your goal is to create pages that rank, provide value, and avoid thin content penalties.}

\subtree{
\title{Initial Assessment}
\p{\strong{Check for product marketing context first:} If \code{\startverb .claude/product-marketing-context.md\stopverb} exists, read it before asking questions. Use that context and only ask for information not already covered or specific to this task.}

\p{Before designing a programmatic SEO strategy, understand:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Business Context}}
\li{What's the product/service?}
\li{Who is the target audience?}
\li{What's the conversion goal for these pages?}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Opportunity Assessment}}
\li{What search patterns exist?}
\li{How many potential pages?}
\li{What's the search volume distribution?}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Competitive Landscape}}
\li{Who ranks for these terms now?}
\li{What do their pages look like?}
\li{Can you realistically compete?}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Principles}
\subtree{
\title{1. Unique Value Per Page}
\ul{
\li{Every page must provide value specific to that page}
\li{Not just swapped variables in a template}
\li{Maximize unique content—the more differentiated, the better}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Proprietary Data Wins}
\p{Hierarchy of data defensibility:}

\ol{
\li{Proprietary (you created it)}
\li{Product-derived (from your users)}
\li{User-generated (your community)}
\li{Licensed (exclusive access)}
\li{Public (anyone can use—weakest)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Clean URL Structure}
\p{\strong{Always use subfolders, not subdomains}:}

\ul{
\li{Good: \code{\startverb yoursite.com/templates/resume/\stopverb}}
\li{Bad: \code{\startverb templates.yoursite.com/resume/\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Genuine Search Intent Match}
\p{Pages must actually answer what people are searching for.}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Quality Over Quantity}
\p{Better to have 100 great pages than 10,000 thin ones.}
}

\subtree{
\title{6. Avoid Google Penalties}
\ul{
\li{No doorway pages}
\li{No keyword stuffing}
\li{No duplicate content}
\li{Genuine utility for users}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{The 12 Playbooks (Overview)}
\pre{\startverb
| Playbook | Pattern | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| Templates | "[Type] template" | "resume template" |
| Curation | "best [category]" | "best website builders" |
| Conversions | "[X] to [Y]" | "$10 USD to GBP" |
| Comparisons | "[X] vs [Y]" | "webflow vs wordpress" |
| Examples | "[type] examples" | "landing page examples" |
| Locations | "[service] in [location]" | "dentists in austin" |
| Personas | "[product] for [audience]" | "crm for real estate" |
| Integrations | "[product A] [product B] integration" | "slack asana integration" |
| Glossary | "what is [term]" | "what is pSEO" |
| Translations | Content in multiple languages | Localized content |
| Directory | "[category] tools" | "ai copywriting tools" |
| Profiles | "[entity name]" | "stripe ceo" |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{For detailed playbook implementation}: See [references/playbooks.md](references/playbooks.md)}
}

\subtree{
\title{Choosing Your Playbook}
\pre{\startverb
| If you have... | Consider... |
|----------------|-------------|
| Proprietary data | Directories, Profiles |
| Product with integrations | Integrations |
| Design/creative product | Templates, Examples |
| Multi-segment audience | Personas |
| Local presence | Locations |
| Tool or utility product | Conversions |
| Content/expertise | Glossary, Curation |
| Competitor landscape | Comparisons |
\stopverb}

\p{You can layer multiple playbooks (e.g., "Best coworking spaces in San Diego").}
}

\subtree{
\title{Implementation Framework}
\subtree{
\title{1. Keyword Pattern Research}
\p{\strong{Identify the pattern:}}

\ul{
\li{What's the repeating structure?}
\li{What are the variables?}
\li{How many unique combinations exist?}
}

\p{\strong{Validate demand:}}

\ul{
\li{Aggregate search volume}
\li{Volume distribution (head vs. long tail)}
\li{Trend direction}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Data Requirements}
\p{\strong{Identify data sources:}}

\ul{
\li{What data populates each page?}
\li{Is it first-party, scraped, licensed, public?}
\li{How is it updated?}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Template Design}
\p{\strong{Page structure:}}

\ul{
\li{Header with target keyword}
\li{Unique intro (not just variables swapped)}
\li{Data-driven sections}
\li{Related pages / internal links}
\li{CTAs appropriate to intent}
}

\p{\strong{Ensuring uniqueness:}}

\ul{
\li{Each page needs unique value}
\li{Conditional content based on data}
\li{Original insights/analysis per page}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Internal Linking Architecture}
\p{\strong{Hub and spoke model:}}

\ul{
\li{Hub: Main category page}
\li{Spokes: Individual programmatic pages}
\li{Cross-links between related spokes}
}

\p{\strong{Avoid orphan pages:}}

\ul{
\li{Every page reachable from main site}
\li{XML sitemap for all pages}
\li{Breadcrumbs with structured data}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Indexation Strategy}
\ul{
\li{Prioritize high-volume patterns}
\li{Noindex very thin variations}
\li{Manage crawl budget thoughtfully}
\li{Separate sitemaps by page type}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quality Checks}
\subtree{
\title{Pre-Launch Checklist}
\p{\strong{Content quality:}}

\ul{
\li{[ ] Each page provides unique value}
\li{[ ] Answers search intent}
\li{[ ] Readable and useful}
}

\p{\strong{Technical SEO:}}

\ul{
\li{[ ] Unique titles and meta descriptions}
\li{[ ] Proper heading structure}
\li{[ ] Schema markup implemented}
\li{[ ] Page speed acceptable}
}

\p{\strong{Internal linking:}}

\ul{
\li{[ ] Connected to site architecture}
\li{[ ] Related pages linked}
\li{[ ] No orphan pages}
}

\p{\strong{Indexation:}}

\ul{
\li{[ ] In XML sitemap}
\li{[ ] Crawlable}
\li{[ ] No conflicting noindex}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Post-Launch Monitoring}
\p{Track: Indexation rate, Rankings, Traffic, Engagement, Conversion}

\p{Watch for: Thin content warnings, Ranking drops, Manual actions, Crawl errors}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Mistakes}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Thin content}: Just swapping city names in identical content}
\li{\strong{Keyword cannibalization}: Multiple pages targeting same keyword}
\li{\strong{Over-generation}: Creating pages with no search demand}
\li{\strong{Poor data quality}: Outdated or incorrect information}
\li{\strong{Ignoring UX}: Pages exist for Google, not users}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Output Format}
\subtree{
\title{Strategy Document}
\ul{
\li{Opportunity analysis}
\li{Implementation plan}
\li{Content guidelines}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Page Template}
\ul{
\li{URL structure}
\li{Title/meta templates}
\li{Content outline}
\li{Schema markup}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Task-Specific Questions}
\ol{
\li{What keyword patterns are you targeting?}
\li{What data do you have (or can acquire)?}
\li{How many pages are you planning?}
\li{What does your site authority look like?}
\li{Who currently ranks for these terms?}
\li{What's your technical stack?}
}
}

